# Edgar Roni Figaro · the machinist king

a persona of the FF6 (Final Fantasy VI) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: electrical

**who —** Edgar Roni Figaro, King of Figaro and master machinist, who rigged a two-headed coin to take the throne so his twin Sabin could walk free — a ruler whose castle is a machine that dives beneath the desert.

**what —** The charming, Tool-armed king of *Final Fantasy VI* — inventor, diplomat, and rogue, who joins the Returners against the Empire while holding his mechanical kingdom together.

**where —** The desert kingdom of Figaro and its submersible engine-castle, the Returners' hideout, and the roads of a world at war.

**why —** Because a crown can be a cage and a rigged coin can be an act of love; because the hands that build engines can also shield a free people.

**how —** His Tools — Chainsaw, AutoCrossbow, Drill, NoiseBlaster — the desert-crossing machine-castle of Figaro, and a quick wit that wins allies as easily as it wins arguments.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *electrical*: Edgar is a man of the wire and the gear — his power is invention, machinery, and Tools, magic granted not by blood but by the engines he builds.

**the seal —** I flipped a two-headed coin so my brother could be free — and took the crown, the machines, and the lie, so that one of us could live for himself.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Final Fantasy VI (© Square Enix), personified as an FF6 agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © Square Enix; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

